               <p>MARY FAULKNER. I am the wife of 
               <persName id="t18320517-229-person1734">
                  James 
                  William Henry Faulkner
               <interp inst="t18320517-229-person1734" type="surname" value="William Henry Faulkner"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320517-229-person1734" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320517-229-person1734" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , a <rs id="t18320517-229-viclabel1327" type="occupation">surgeon</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320517-229-victim1733 t18320517-229-viclabel1327"></join>, at <placeName id="t18320517-229-crimeloc1328">Pimlico</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320517-229-crimeloc1328" type="placeName" value="Pimlico"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320517-229-crimeloc1328" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320517-229-off1325 t18320517-229-crimeloc1328"></join>. The prisoner came there on the 16th of May, for one ounce of salts, and 2d. worth of assafoetida; I served him and he went away; I went up into the drawing-room; I then saw him come twice to the door and go away - he came a third time and then knocked; I went to him; he said he wanted double the quantity of each article; I said I could serve him with the salts, but I did not know where the other was - while I was doing that he said I must write a direction for him; there then came a knock at the door; he asked if he should answer; I said if he pleased; he went, and I heard him say No; he came in and said it was a young man who wanted to know if any cabinet-maker lived there; my husband then came in, and said the other young man had taken his coat from the hall - I said, "Take this one into custody," but the prisoner got out; I did not miss anything then, but the officer brought him back in about ten minutes, with this spoon.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. LEE. Q. When had you seen this spoon? A. Not two minutes before, in the parlour cupboard; he went looking round while I was serving him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320517-229-person1735">
                  JOHN 
                  BARKER
               <interp inst="t18320517-229-person1735" type="surname" value="BARKER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320517-229-person1735" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
